---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Built in the Open - Open Integration Engine"
  description="Open Integration Engine is developed in the open. Public code, public releases, public governance, on a path to Eclipse Foundation stewardship."
>
  <article class="page">
    <PageHero
      title="Built in the open."
      lead="No private forks. No insider builds. No walled-off releases."
    />

    <section>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="card card--padded">
          <h2>Where the work happens</h2>
          <p>
            OIE is developed on <a href="https://github.com/OpenIntegrationEngine" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
            Every code change is a public commit. Every bug, feature request, and design
            discussion is a <a href="https://github.com/OpenIntegrationEngine/engine/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener">public issue</a>
            or <a href="https://github.com/OpenIntegrationEngine/engine/discussions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">discussion thread</a>.
            Every <a href="https://github.com/OpenIntegrationEngine/engine/releases" target="_blank" rel="noopener">release</a>
            ships from a repository you can audit.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="card card--padded">
          <h2>Governance</h2>
          <p>
            The engine is led by a public
            <a href="https://github.com/OpenIntegrationEngine/governance/blob/main/steering_committee.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Steering Committee</a>
            and a group of
            <a href="https://github.com/OpenIntegrationEngine/governance/blob/main/maintainers.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maintainers</a>,
            with Contributors at every level. Selection, responsibilities, and decision-making
            are documented in the
            <a href="https://github.com/OpenIntegrationEngine/governance" target="_blank" rel="noopener">governance repository</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="card card--padded">
          <h2>Headed for the Eclipse Foundation</h2>
          <p>
            OIE has begun the process of joining the
            <a href="https://www.eclipse.org/org/foundation/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Eclipse Foundation</a>,
            the same stewardship structure that backs Jakarta EE, Theia, and Jetty. It is a
            multi-year path, but the direction is set: long-term institutional openness, not
            just a friendly license.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="card card--padded">
          <h2>How to contribute</h2>
          <p>
            Everything is on GitHub.
            <a href="https://github.com/OpenIntegrationEngine/engine/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open an issue</a>,
            <a href="https://github.com/OpenIntegrationEngine/engine/discussions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">start a discussion</a>,
            or <a href="https://github.com/OpenIntegrationEngine/engine/pulls" target="_blank" rel="noopener">send a pull request</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page { padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
  section { padding: 1rem 0; }
  section:last-of-type { padding-bottom: 4rem; }
  .card h2 { margin: 0 0 1rem; text-align: center; font-size: var(--font-size-section-h2); }
  .card p { margin: 0; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .card a { font-weight: 600; }
</style>
